      "content": "Escrow is essentially a neutral third-party account where funds and documents are held during a real estate transaction. Its primary purpose is to act as a secure holding place, ensuring that all agreed-upon conditions of the sale are met before any money or property title is transferred. This protects both the buyer and the seller from disputes or defaults during the closing period.",
