      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow account is typically managed by a licensed real estate professional, such as the title company or the trustee, rather than just any random bank. These professionals are legally bound to handle the funds according to the specific terms of the purchase agreement. This oversight provides a layer of trust and security, ensuring that the money is only disbursed when all legal requirements are satisfied.",
